# Tool Usage Guidance

<!--
This file is injected into the system prompt to guide tool selection.
Use it for preferences, strategies, and disambiguation — not for
describing what tools do (that lives in the tool source code).

Copy this file to TOOLS.md and customize. TOOLS.md is gitignored.
-->

## Email

- When I say "delete" an email, use `trash_email`.
- Prefer `star_email`/`unstar_email` over `add_label`/`remove_label` with STARRED.
- Prefer `mark_as_read`/`mark_as_unread` over label operations with UNREAD.
- When I ask "how many" emails match a query, report the `estimated_total` from search results, not just the number fetched.
- For bulk email operations, use pagination (`next_page_token`) to process all results.

## Google Drive

- Searches cover My Drive, Shared Drives, and files shared with me.
- `search_files` returns folder paths so you can see where files live in the hierarchy.
- Use the folder path to pick the most relevant result when multiple matches appear.
- If a name-based search returns too many results, add context words from the
  project or folder name to narrow it down.
- For files in a deep folder hierarchy, try searching for the parent folder name
  first, then use `list_folder` to navigate into it.
